The response of list API is —

```{
    "runs": [
        {
            "id": "d46e0a3a-ec5d-42da-939e-304746ce25d1",
            "status": "COMPLETE",
            "msg": "Completed single_flow",
            "start_timestamp": "1728333401440822066",
            "finish_timestamp": "1728333448891210629"
        }
    ],
    "has_more": false,
    "next_offset": -1
}```
We defined timestamp to be int64 in api.yaml, it throws an error parsing this response.

As this Run object is created based on different job status, the type of timestamp is not always consistent (either str or int), in the PR I make it int so that it’s also compatible with SDK
